choose_kemetic_cult_desc;As a Kemetic I must choose one of the Divine Eigth to worship.;;;;;;;;;x
wonder_pyramid_memphis_desc;This pyramid was built by order of Pharaoh Klemens
column2: the founder of the first Mississippi Empire. Tradition has it that the Pharaoh had the pyramid built on top of the remains of an antediviludian pyramid that was too damaged to be restored.;;;;;;;;;x

column1: EVTDESC_delver_300;All Delvers are part of a Lodge
column2: and now I must make a decision of which one I shall join.;;;;;;;;;x

choose_delver_cult_desc;As a Delver I must choose one of the four main Lodges to join.;;;;;;;;;x

column2: these Charioteers represent the power and chivalry of the lands of Egypt. Established under the rule of Klemens I
column3: they have long since changed and have adopted heavier armor from Cahokia while keeping their unique Kemetic style.;;;;;;;;;;;;;x

column1: ca_culture_watcher_1_desc;The Watchers's main force live in these buildings
column2: ready for battle at a minute's notice. The Watchman pledge their whole lives to defend and fight for christiandom and thus are counted as the Order's most elite troops on the battlefield regardless of their rank within the Order. With some higher ranking and skilled members fighting on the field as Heavy Cavalry.;;;;;;;;;;;;;x

column1: ca_culture_mis_auxilia_1_desc;Coming from the border regions of the Upper Mississippi or smaller groups within it
column2: these men form the first response to any attack on its borders.;;;;;;;;;;;;;x
protectors of the east coast german communities. These men come from those who wish to protect their homeland and families from the ever changing times the Old Order's believers are facing
column3: giving up their way of life so others may continue to practice it in peace from foreign invaders.;;;;;;;;;;;;;x

column1: ca_culture_azure_1_desc;The Companions are the elite of the Mississipian Armies
column2: these trained soldiers come from the core regions of the Mississippi and excel in urban combat. Originally the soldiers under the commmand of at the time Prince Basil I
column3: they have been expended in role during his later conquests as Azure Emperor. They have since been divided into many smaller companies of Men-At-Arms
column4: whos loyalty may be closer to that of their local ruler then the Azure Throne.;;;;;;;;;;;;;x

column1: ca_culture_federalist_1_desc;The Columbian Minutemen are masters of rifle and musket combat
column2: outmaneuvering any foe while unleashing volleys of musket fire.;;;;;;;;;;;;;x

column1: ca_culture_dominion_1_desc;The Royal Mounties are men of the saddle and sword
column2: being expert skirmishers and heavy cavalry. They uphold their ancient duty to protect the lands of Canada be enforcing law or fighting on the battlefield.;;;;;;;;;;;;;x

column1: ca_culture_southron_1_desc;Southron Skirmishers make use of their light cavalry in massive charges while harassing their foes with their gunpowder wielding units.;;;;;;;;;;;;;x
ca_culture_gaoshan_1_desc;The Crossbowmen of Gaoshan are one of the best skirmishers the East Coast has to offer
column2: having exceptional training from an early age and knowledge of their homeland.;;;;;;;;;;;;;x

column1: ca_culture_usa_camel_1_desc;Camelry is an unique phenomenon among the people of the Southwest
column2: with tales told of a far away land called "Africa" where their ancestors brought them from. Camels have become the most widely used mounts in these regions thanks to their adaption to the climate and large population thanks to wild populations and breeding.;;;;;;;;;;;;;x

column1: ca_culture_east_texas_1_desc;Texan Gunslingers are one of the few men left who continue the use of gunpowder. Their use of roughly made firearms has made them legendary among tribals
column2: nomads and settled peoples alike in the lands of the Old West.;;;;;;;;;;;;;x

column1: invite_local_turk_desc;Invite a Türk man from your local Türk community.;;;;;;;;;;x
invite_local_turk_woman_desc;Invite a Türk woman from your local Türk community.;;;;;;;;;;x

column1: religion_feature_novelist_2_desc;Our customs from over the sea hold that we must keep our blood pure
column2: our seed strong
